{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e61a4f4f-0a34-4b0f-93d6-534210aa7b2e","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages with major version bumps (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) and update those to their 11.x versions as well.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5e64d464-2fa7-4c14-951b-3e149a1c2ab8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the specific files and values.","outputTokens":283},"id":"27ed7e8a-beec-4761-8ed1-c7288c76c475","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:59:56.412Z","parentId":"dd948f00-2167-4354-ae2a-61235cd763f4"}
